What is CSS and why do we need it ?

CSS - Cascading Style Sheets

Cascade - you can conjure a pic of cascade, it's like waterfall. The way the styles are applied cascades like
a waterfall. We start from the most general all the way down to the most specific styling requirements.


Style Sheets - is a type of language, similarly how we have html that is markup language
is a language that specifies how things should look in our website.
There are other types of Style Sheets
- CSS - most important one is css
- Sass - syntactically awesome style sheet
- Less - Leaner CSS
- many others


why do we need css?
developers wanted to style their website but html was very limited in that
sense.

previously styling was done in html itself, but it cluttered the html file, it's deprecated now,
then css was introduced, which can be attached the style sheet to the html file components.
